The paper deals with proof complexity, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the analysis of communication protocols, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DS). The use of polynomials and polynomial threshold functions suggests connections to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds and hierarchies, which are common topics in logic and computation (cs.LO).
